  <refnamediv xml:id="lms">
    <refname>lms</refname>

    <refpurpose>Least-Mean-Squared Rule(Widrow-Hoff) (for two-category
    cases)</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>

    <synopsis>[a, test_labels] = lms(train_samples, train_labels, param, test_samples)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsection>
    <title>Parameters</title>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>train_samples</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>training data matrix of size dim*num_tr; each column is a data
          point</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>train_labels</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>1*num_tr vector of labels for the training samples</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>param</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>parameters for the criterion, including the maximum number of
          iterations, the convergence criterion and the convergence rate:
          [iterm,theta,eta]; The default value is [1000,0.01,0.1]</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>test_samples</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>test data matrix of size dim*num_te; each column is a data
          point</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>a</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>weight vector</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>test_labels</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>predicted labels for the test samples</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>

  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>

    <para>The function finds a linear classifier using least mean squared
    rule.</para>
  </refsection>

